                <note rend="inline" type="source">500. A 4e/101: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-27T12:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 27, 1922—12 noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>235. Communicate following to Arnold:</p>
                <p>Your undated telegrams received September 9 and September 13.</p>
                <p>Ratifications Customs Treaty, pursuant to which Commission is proceeding, not
                    deposited as provided Article 10 and consequently treaty not in force. However,
                    Department will interpose no objections to publication revised schedule in
                    manner indicated your September 13 pending deposit of ratifications provided
                    schedule is accepted by all of the interested governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
